    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im a site foreman and need a quick refresher/checklist for the mandatory safety checks we gotta do on residential scaffolding before anyone climbs it. what are the main things to look for?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "As a site foreman, your priority checklist must focus on verifying base stability, ensuring all guardrails and toeboards are intact, and confirming that every plank is securely anchored with no gaps. You also need to inspect the entire system for any visible rust, cracks, or loose pins that could compromise structural integrity before workers access the platform. Don't forget to verify that the scaffold passes muster with your local authority's specific regulations before allowing anyone to climb onto it.",
