    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. and what about the connections? like the couplers and braces? we get a lot of wind on these sites so i want to make sure the thing doesn't just rattle apart or buckle when things get intense.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since you are dealing with windy conditions, give every right-angle and swivel coupler a tightness check by applying the manufacturer's required torque with a wrench. Inspect all metal braces and diagonal members for absence of rust, twist, or dent that could weaken their load-bearing capacity during high winds. Finally, ensure every screwed pin is fully seated and every bolt is thread-locked to prevent vibration-induced loosening while climbing.",
